📌 Phase-Wise Correction Plan
Project: Kavi Cakes Order Management System
Purpose: Fix existing functional, navigation, pricing, loyalty, order flow, and validation issues across all order types (Normal, Custom, Bulk)

🔹 PHASE 1 – Global UI, Navigation & Data Consistency Fixes
1. Navigation Bar & Page Recognition


Fix navigation so that:


The currently active page is visually highlighted in the navigation bar.


Users can clearly identify which page they are currently on.




Ensure route recognition works correctly for all navigation links.


2. Home Page Navigation Corrections


Custom Order buttons:


Every button related to “Custom Order” must navigate to the Custom Order Page.




Browse by Category section:


Clicking a category must navigate to the respective Category Page.


Category pages must display all cakes belonging to that category.




Featured Cakes section:


Featured cakes must be the most recently added cakes by the admin.


Clicking View Details must navigate to the Cake Details Page.




Remove the Community section completely.


3. Global Price Display Rule


Wherever cake prices are displayed (home, category, listings, featured cakes):


Always display the 1kg variant price only.





🔹 PHASE 2 – Cake Listing & Cake Detail Page Corrections
1. Birthday Cake Page


Display price as 1kg price only for all cakes.


2. Cake Detail Page


Show all available variant prices (e.g., 500g, 1kg, 1.5kg, etc.).


Remove allergen information.


Enable Save Cake / Wishlist functionality.


When quantity increases:


Total price must update dynamically based on quantity × selected variant price.





🔹 PHASE 3 – Cart, Loyalty Points & Delivery Date Logic
1. Add to Cart & Loyalty Points


Correctly calculate loyalty points per order.


Assign earned loyalty points to the relevant logged-in customer account.


Display:


Earned loyalty points for the current order.


Total loyalty points balance correctly.




2. Delivery Date Validation (Common for Normal, Custom & Bulk Orders)


Prevent selecting past dates.


If customer selects a near date (e.g., day after tomorrow):


System must prompt the user to use/burn loyalty points.


If user confirms burning points → allow continuation.


If not → block the selection.




Ensure the same logic applies consistently across:


Normal orders


Custom orders


Bulk orders





🔹 PHASE 4 – Payment Rules & Checkout Validation
1. Payment Type Logic


Cash on Delivery (COD):


Customers must NOT be able to select advance or partial payment.


Full payment is mandatory on delivery.




Bank Payment:


Customer can place order without payment.


After admin approval, customer can upload bank slip.




2. Checkout Page Fixes


Ensure order summary correctly displays:


Total amount


Loyalty points earned




Disable Advance Payment radio button when COD is selected.


Ensure checkout → place order flow works without missing data.



🔹 PHASE 5 – Order Tracking, Cancellation & Editing Rules
1. Order Tracking Page


Do Payment button:


Must navigate to Upload Bank Slip Page.




Remove Help / Need Help section.


2. Cancel Order


Allow cancellation only within 2 days from order placement.


On cancellation:


Remove all related order records.


Update loyalty points accordingly.




3. Edit Order


Allow editing only within 2 days.


Redirect customer to Cart Page with order details loaded.


4. My Orders Section


Orders must be filtered by status:


Pending


In Progress


Delivered





